<subSubSection id="C33E6531CC54FFE3FF38CFDDFE1CFAD8" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC54FFE3FF38CFDDFC92FC4C" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FF38CFDDFE8AFC68" bold="true" box="[199,334,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific designation 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FD95CFDDFD11FC68" authorityName="Xue &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[618,725,943,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Calepitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liuanense">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FD95CFDDFD11FC68" box="[618,725,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">liuanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the name of location, Liuan city, where the new species was collected, adding a postfix - 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FDA6CFA1FD4FFC4D" box="[601,651,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">ense</emphasis>
; neuter in gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B36BACC54FFE3FF38CF84FE1CFAD8" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FF38CF84FE0EFBB1" bold="true" box="[199,458,1014,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Deferential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FC1ECF85FB36FBB0" authority="Kuang, 1991" authorityName="Kuang" authorityYear="1991" box="[993,1266,1015,1041]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Chamaecyparis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FC1ECF85FB9DFBB0" box="[993,1113,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">C. sabinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC54FFE3FB9FCF85FB36FBB0" author="Kuang, H. - Y." box="[1120,1266,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" pagination="99 - 102" refId="ref7913" refString="Kuang, H. - Y. (1991) Three new species of Phyllocoptinae from China (Acariformes: Eriophyidae). Acta Entomologica Sinica, 34 (1), 99 - 102." type="journal article" year="1991">Kuang, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by body shape and prodorsal shield design, which infest 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FD79C869FCACFB94" box="[646,872,1051,1077]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FD79C869FCACFB94" box="[646,872,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Juniperus chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FC60C869FBFAFB94" box="[927,1086,1051,1077]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cupressaceae</taxonomicName>
), but can be differentiated by prodorsal shield with admedian and submedian lines (prodorsal shield smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FBC1C84DFB7CFBF8" authorityName="Kuang" authorityYear="1991" box="[1086,1208,1087,1113]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Chamaecyparis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FBC1C84DFB7CFBF8" box="[1086,1208,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">C. sabinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and empodium 4- rayed (empodium 6-rayed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FE19C811FDA4FBDC" authorityName="Kuang" authorityYear="1991" box="[486,608,1123,1149]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Chamaecyparis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FE19C811FDA4FBDC" box="[486,608,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">C. sabinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FBF7C811FF0BFB00" authority="Xue &amp; Yin, 2020" authorityName="Xue &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Leipothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FBF7C811FACAFBDD" box="[1032,1294,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Leipothrix juniperensis</emphasis>
Xue &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC54FFE3FA92C811FF0BFB00" author="Yin, Y. &amp; Yao, L. - F. &amp; Zhang, Q. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N. &amp; Xue, X. - F." pageId="4" pageNumber="283" pagination="757 - 768" refId="ref9452" refString="Yin, Y., Yao, L. - F., Zhang, Q., Hebert, P. D. N. &amp; Xue, X. - F. (2020) Using multiple lines of evidence to delimit protogynes and deutogynes of four-legged mites: a case study on Epitrimerus sabinae s. l. (Acari: Eriophyidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 34, 757 - 768. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 20014" type="journal article" year="2020">Yin, 2020</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(infesting 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FEB8C8F5FE0CFB00" box="[327,456,1159,1185]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FEB8C8F5FE0CFB00" box="[327,456,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">J. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC54FFE3FE2AC8F5FDBFFB00" author="Yin, Y. &amp; Yao, L. - F. &amp; Zhang, Q. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N. &amp; Xue, X. - F." box="[469,635,1159,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" pagination="757 - 768" refId="ref9452" refString="Yin, Y., Yao, L. - F., Zhang, Q., Hebert, P. D. N. &amp; Xue, X. - F. (2020) Using multiple lines of evidence to delimit protogynes and deutogynes of four-legged mites: a case study on Epitrimerus sabinae s. l. (Acari: Eriophyidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 34, 757 - 768. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 20014" type="journal article" year="2020">
Yin 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FDFBC8F5FDF0FB00" box="[516,564,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
) by body shape and prodorsal shield design, but can be differentiated by pedipalp genual setae (
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FE69C8D9FE60FB64" box="[406,420,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">d</emphasis>
) uniform (pedipalp genual setae 
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FCEDC8D9FCE4FB64" box="[786,800,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">d</emphasis>
bifurcated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FC45C8D9FB9BFB65" authorityName="Xue &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2020" box="[954,1119,1195,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Leipothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FC45C8D9FB9BFB65" box="[954,1119,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">L. juniperensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), middorsal ridge ended in a broad furrow (middorsal ridge as long as subdorsal ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FCC6C8BDFC19FB49" authorityName="Xue &amp; Yin" authorityYear="2020" box="[825,989,1231,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Leipothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FCC6C8BDFC19FB49" box="[825,989,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">L. juniperensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Furthermore, the new specie is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FF4AC881FDBEFAAC" authority="Xue &amp; Hong, 2005" authorityName="Xue &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2005" box="[181,634,1266,1293]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Epitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FF4AC881FE5DFAAC" box="[181,409,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Epitrimerus sabinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B4BCC54FFE3FE5EC881FDBEFAAC" author="Xue, X. - F. &amp; Hong, X. - Y." box="[417,634,1266,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref9116" refString="Xue, X. - F. &amp; Hong, X. - Y. (2005) A new genus and eight new species of Phyllocoptini (Acari: Eriophyidae: Phyllocoptinae) from China. Zootaxa, 1039, 1 - 17. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1039.1.1" type="journal article" year="2005">Xue &amp; Hong, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(infesting 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FD0AC881FCBCFAAC" box="[757,888,1267,1293]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FD0AC881FCBCFAAC" box="[757,888,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">J. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by body shape and prodorsal shield design, but can be differentiated by middorsal ridge ended in a broad furrow (middorsal ridge as long as subdorsal ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FA7BC965FF2AFAF4" authorityName="Xue &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2005" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Epitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FA7BC965FF2AFAF4" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">E. sabinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dorsal annuli smooth (dorsal annuli with microtubercles in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FC54C949FBE7FAF4" authorityName="Xue &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2005" box="[939,1059,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Epitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FC54C949FBE7FAF4" box="[939,1059,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">E. sabinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and empodium 4-rayed (empodium 6-rayed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D39CC54FFE3FEAEC92DFE03FAD8" authorityName="Xue &amp; Hong" authorityYear="2005" box="[337,455,1375,1401]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Epitrimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabinae">
<emphasis id="B950EAA8CC54FFE3FEAEC92DFE03FAD8" box="[337,455,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">E. sabinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
